                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.4181/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-08T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your despatch 333 of July 20. Please inform the Department by telegraph in
                    Gray Code: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The precise terms of any protest which the Dean contemplates making to
                            the French Protectorate authorities;</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>The countries represented by those of your colleagues who have
                            signified their intention of associating themselves with such a protest;
                            and</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>The character of any views, which may have been formulated by your
                            colleagues, contrary to those entertained by the Dean, so far as they
                            may be available.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
